The nonrefundable § 24 credit reduces regular tax after FTC at US25-21 (it cannot offset the § 1411 NIIT, § 55 AMT, § 1401 SE tax, or § 3101(b)(2) Additional Medicare Tax — those are separate additional taxes). The § 24(d) refundable ACTC is added to payments on the same line.

